

Parchi MVP: A Strategic Development Partnership

*Proposed by Aawaiz Ali, Hashir Khan & Umer Noor*

*Version: 1.4*

*Thursday, 22nd November, 2025*

**Project Overview**  
This proposal outlines the development of a minimal viable product (MVP) for "Parchi," a secure, student verification-based discount redemption platform for students and merchants. We have refined the original technical scope to leverage more modern, scalable, and efficient technologies, ensuring a robust foundation for future growth.

**Proposed Revised Tech Stack**  
Our recommended stack is chosen for its performance, developer efficiency, and long-term scalability.

| Layer | Technology | Justification |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Mobile App | Flutter | A single codebase for high-performance iOS and Android apps, ensuring faster development and a consistent user experience. |
| Backend | NestJS | A progressive Node.js framework that provides an out-of-the-box application architecture, making the code more maintainable, testable, and scalable than standard Express.js. |
| Web Dashboards | Next.js (PWA) | Enables fast, SEO-friendly React-based Progressive Web Applications for Merchant and Admin dashboards with server-side rendering capabilities and app-like experience. |
| Database & Auth | Supabase | An open-source Firebase alternative built on PostgreSQL. It provides instant authentication, real-time databases, and secure APIs, simplifying backend development and reducing costs. |
| Push Notifications | Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) | The industry standard for reliable and free push notifications on both iOS and Android. |
| Hosting | Vercel (Web) / Railway (Backend) | Modern, developer-friendly hosting platforms that offer seamless deployment and excellent performance. |

### **1\. MVP Feature Set (Refined & Confirmed)**

#### **Student App (Flutter)**

* Signup & Annual KYC Verification: Register by uploading student ID and a selfie. All accounts remain "Pending" until manually reviewed and approved by an admin. Students must re-verify their status annually to maintain account validity.  
* Unique Parchi ID: Upon verification, each student receives a unique alphanumeric Parchi ID (e.g., PK-12345) displayed prominently in the app.  
* Student Dashboard:  
  * View active merchant offers with Basic Filtering (e.g., by category, proximity, popularity).  
  * View Personal Parchi ID for easy redemption.  
  * Simple Student Leaderboard: A tap-to-view button reveals a leaderboard showcasing top students based on total savings or redemptions.  
  * Redemption History: A simple log of all past redemptions.  
  * Basic Analytics: View personal stats like "Total Saved."  
  * Founders Club: A cosmetic sign or symbol that indicates that the student is a part of the Founder’s Club  
* Flexible Redemption System: Two seamless redemption workflows using the Parchi ID:  
  * Walk-in Kiosk Ordering:  
    * Students provide their Parchi ID to the cashier.  
    * The cashier enters the ID into the Merchant Dashboard.  
    * The redemption request is verified and approved by the cashier, who manually applies the discount.  
    * Students receive an approval notification.  
  * Dine-in Ordering:  
    * Students provide their Parchi ID to the server/cashier.  
    * Cashier enters the ID into the Merchant Dashboard to trigger the redemption request.  
    * The cashier verifies and approves the request, applying the discount manually to the final bill.  
* Automatic Reward System:  
  * Students automatically unlock an exclusive "Bonus Discount" for every 5 successful redemptions they make at the same merchant.  
  * These bonus discounts are automatically applied to their account and visible in a dedicated "Available Rewards" section, requiring no manual effort from the student to "earn" them.

#### **Merchant Dashboard (Next.js PWA)**

* Authentication: Secure login/signup (requires admin approval).  
* Hierarchical Account Structure:  
  * Corporate Account: Create and manage branch accounts; Master analytics across all branches including transaction logs, user footfall, payables to Parchi, and full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) capabilities for offers.  
  * Branch Account: A streamlined interface focused solely on verifying student Parchi IDs (via manual entry) and approving redemption requests in real-time.  
* Real-time Redemption Panel: Live interface for verifying student memberships by manually entering their Parchi ID.  
* Advanced Analytics: View redemption counts and exportable reports, with full financial and footfall data for corporate accounts.

#### **Admin Dashboard (Next.js PWA)**

* Manual KYC Management: Review and approve/reject student registrations and annual re-verifications.  
* User Management: Approve or reject merchant registrations (both corporate and branch).  
* Offer Oversight: View, approve, or remove offers created by merchants.  
* System Logs: Monitor all redemption activities and system events with branch-branded transaction tracking.

### **2\. Development Timeline & Milestone**

Total Duration: 4-5 Weeks

| Week | Focus | Key Deliverables |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Week 1 | Foundation & KYC Setup | Project setup, finalized DB schema, Supabase auth integration, and implementation of manual student verification workflow. |
| Week 2 | Core Redemption Logic | Full implementation of both kiosk and dine-in redemption workflows, including QR code generation and real-time request handling. |
| Week 3 | Dashboard Development (PWA) | Fully functional Merchant and Admin PWAs for offers, real-time verification, user management, and analytics. |
| Week 4-5 | Polishing & Deployment | Rigorous QA testing, bug fixes, and deployment of the backend, PWAs, and mobile app to TestFlight/Play Store. |

### **4\. Post-MVP Support & Maintenance**

Following the successful launch of the **Parchi MVP**, **Aawaiz Ali**, will remain available **on retainer** to ensure the platform’s stability, security, and continued performance.

This retainer will cover:

* **Bug Fixes & Issue Resolution:** Addressing any post-launch technical glitches or performance issues.

* **System Monitoring:** Keeping backend services, APIs, and dashboards stable and responsive.

* **Minor Feature Enhancements:** Implementing small improvements or UI/UX refinements as feedback is gathered from real users.

* **Security & Token Validation Checks:** Ensuring the token-based redemption system remains secure and tamper-proof.

* **Deployment & Infrastructure Support:** Managing updates, redeployments, and any hosting-related configurations.

The retainer will be structured as a monthly maintenance plan, ensuring dedicated support and fast turnaround times as the product moves from MVP to a fully operational platform. Additionally, we will provide **one month of complimentary post-delivery support** exclusively for bug fixes and technical assistance, **no additional feature development will be included during this period.**

To ensure complete transparency, we will maintain a **Trello board and a Discord Server** for real-time progress tracking. While you are welcome to have an external developer audit our progress through Trello, we request that all communication and project direction come directly from you to maintain workflow efficiency and avoid micromanagement.

Our architecture is designed to be future-ready, with a modular foundation that seamlessly accommodates upcoming features like **Parchi Pakistan Plus**, **NFC redemption, and POS integrations.**

We are confident that our technical expertise and startup mindset make us the ideal partner to bring **Parchi** to life. We are excited about the opportunity to collaborate with you.
